    • timeClash

      public boolean timeClash​(int checkDay, int existDay, java.util.Date start1, java.util.Date end1, java.util.Date start2, java.util.Date end2)
      Method to check if timing of new lessons added clash with existing registered lessons
      Parameters:
      checkDay - The lesson day of the incoming course.
      existDay - The lesson day of existing registered courses.
      start1 - The start timing of the incoming lessons.
      end1 - The end timing of the incoming lessons.
      start2 - The start timing of the existing registered lessons.
      end2 - The end timing of the existing registered lessons.
      Returns:
      a boolean: true if timing clash, false if there are no clashes

    • checkClash

      public boolean checkClash​(Schedule otherSch)
      Uses timeClash method to check conflict of timing of the different types of lessons of the new course that is to be added with the different types of lessons of the existing registered courses. Informs user which lessons clash with which existing type of lesson.
      Parameters:
      otherSch - Takes in the schedule of the incoming course.
      Returns:
      true if it clashes, false if it does not clash.
